# server/.dockerignore — Controls what the Docker build context sends to the daemon.
#
# The build context is everything under server/ sent to Docker on every
# "docker-compose up --build". Without this file Docker sends ~50 MB
# (public/ alone is 31 MB). With it, only the Go source is sent.
#
# Rule: the builder stage copies each Go package dir explicitly, so Docker
# only needs those. public/ is copied by the runtime stage via COPY public/,
# which still works because .dockerignore exclusions apply to the context
# sent to the daemon — the COPY instruction in the Dockerfile still resolves
# from inside the context. We must NOT exclude public/ here because the
# runtime stage needs it. What we exclude is everything else that is large
# and not needed by either stage.

# ── Never needed by any stage ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Local persistent data — never goes into an image
data/

# Docker and Make files — already consumed by the daemon, not needed inside
Dockerfile*
docker-compose.yml
Makefile
README.md
*.sh

# Go test cache and tool artifacts
**/*_test.go
**/*.test

# Editor and OS noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/
